Trim the @carrot{1}, then quarter lengthways (no need to peel). Chop widthways into small pieces. Trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leek{1}. Slice into rounds about 0.5cm thick. Halve the @red chilli{1/2} lengthways, remove the seeds then finely chop.

Pick both the @thyme{1/2} leaves and the @sage{1/2} leaves from their stalks (discard the stalks from both herbs). Roughly chop the sage leaves.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} over medium heat. Add the carrot, leek, and to start with, a pinch of chilli (you can add more or less depending on how much you like spice!) and all of the thyme and sage. Season with @salt{} and cook gently until soft, ~{8-9%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

> Turn the heat down if the ingredients start to brown.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium high heat. Season the @British chicken thighs{4} with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Once the #pan{} is hot, lay in the chicken skin side down and fry until the skin is golden and crisp, ~{5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw chicken.

Once golden, turn and cook for ~{5%minutes} on the other side, then continue cooking, turning every ~{2%minutes} for 4-6 more mins or until the chicken is cooked through.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the chicken cooks, drain and rinse the @lentils{1} in a #sieve{}. Once the veggies are soft, add the lentils along with a splash of water, @chicken stock powder{1} and @creme fraiche{99}. Stir to dissolve the stock powder, bring to the boil and then remove from the heat. Season to taste with salt and pepper if needed.

> Add more chilli if you want it spicier!

Spoon the spiced creamy lentils onto your plates and top with the pan-fried chicken. Enjoy!